<HEADLINE>
LIVE-FIRE DRILL OF ANNUAL HAN KUANG EXERCISE BEGINS
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Taipei, May 14 (CNA) 05/14/07  21:41:52 (By Lilian Wu)
</P>
<P>
The live-fire drill of the annual Han Kuang 23 military exercise
kicked off the five-day wargames Monday, according to the
Ministry of National Defense (MND).
</P>
<P>
MND officials  said the combined  forces warfare operation
conducted on Taiwan proper as well as on outlying islands are to
practice takeoffs and landings on emergency runways and the
overall defense capability of military bases, as well as other
training items.
</P>
<P>
The officials noted that compared with previous years, the
exercise this year is the largest, involving the most
participants, the highest level of combined forces and the most
comprehensive training programs.
</P>
<P>
To enhance public understanding of national security,  the
ministry also asked the military units taking part in the live-
fire exercise to set up several viewing points in Penghu,
Hualien, Yilan, Hsinchu, Taichung, Changhua and Pingtung.
</P>
